<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
<title>@KJ{{what}}</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="japanese.css"/>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
</head>

@GRMIDX{{index="@HI{{nani}} (pronunciation)" grammar="@KJ{{what}} (pronunciation)"}}

<body>

<h1>@KJ{{what}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @KJ{{what}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
The interrogative @KJ{{what}} is pronounced as either @HI{{nani}} or as @HI{{nann}}.
</p>

<p>
@HI{{nann}} is used in the following cases:
<ol>
<li> before a word whose first mora is in the @HI{{ta}}, @HI{{da}} or @HI{{na}} row:
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{korehanandesuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What is that?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<br/>
<br/>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{nannno@KJ{{hon}}desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What is that book about?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<br/>
<br/>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{lie*down}}rumaeni,nanto@KJ{{say}}imasuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What do you say before going to bed?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<br/>
<br/>
<li> before a counter suffix or similar:
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{teresa}}chanha nann@KJ{{year-end}}desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      How old is Teresa?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<p>
In all other cases the pronunciation is @HI{{nani}}:

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{naniwo@KJ{{buy}}imasuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What will you buy?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<h2> References </h2>

<ol>
<li> @REF{{MNN-TR-I}}. (Chapter 6).
</ol>

@include{{"grammar-footer.inc"}}

</body>

</html>
